1
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:04,680
Oh no.
-What’s going on? What happened?

2
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:06,240
The brat.
-Saharuf?

3
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:09,080
No, I forgot to bring Itamar his "Bari."

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,800
The phone?
-That’s not good.

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:12,760
Alright, son, just bring it to him next week.

6
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:14,800
Are you crazy? That’s his "Bari."

7
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:17,240
What do you want? Just come back home and take it to him.

8
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:19,640
No, I’m not turning back,
he’s already on his way to your parents'.

9
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,080
Fine, okay, he can wait a few minutes.

10
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,320
Alone.

11
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,760
Yeah, alone, what could possibly happen?

12
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,640
With Itamar, anything can happen.

13
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:28,880
You have no idea what disasters
he’s caused and will cause.

14
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:32,640
When they set up an inquiry committee,
they’ll find out that in the Passover Haggadah,

15
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:34,120
it was him who sold the goat to Dad.

16
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,560
Alright, so what do you want?

17
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,280
I’ll take the girls upstairs to keep an eye on him

18
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:39,680
and you go get him his "Bari."

19
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,120
Hey, is there a chance you’ll come back
and I’ll go down with the girls to Grandma’s?

20
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,720
Yeah, no problem, babe, sure.

21
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:46,680
He has.

22
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:48,200
I’ll go back home, you go down with them.

23
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:55,840
Look at me, look at me and...

24
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,840
Hey, babe, don’t you think you’re overreacting a bit?

25
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,160
Not at all.

26
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,960
What happened? It’s just your brother,
why do you always make a mountain out of a molehill?

27
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,480
It’s funny, come on.

28
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:18,120
What “come on”? What, what, what could possibly happen?

29
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,920
I can already see myself if I come back,

30
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,760
I see you two holding each other by the throat.

31
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:24,120
The Hasson family test, oh, you forgot about that.

32
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,200
Alright, I can already see myself searching, like a detective,

33
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:29,120
where it all started, what happened,
only to find Itamar sitting there, smiling.

34
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,280
I think you forgot who you married.

35
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:33,600
Half an hour, babe.
-Go, take your time, what’s the problem?

36
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,520
Half an hour.
-Alright.

37
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,560
Good luck.
-Thanks.

38
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,720
You know!

39
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:40,080
That I loved you.
-Yeah, there was a rumor about that once.

40
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,080
Benon, at home.

41
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:49,720
Are you hearing what I’m saying?
It’s only fair that you and Mavi be partners.

42
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,960
But you’re not willing to be my partner.
-Why are you interfering?

43
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:54,920
She’s his sister, she can interfere.
-Enough with this behavior, that’s enough.

44
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,480
I want to be part of the group too.

45
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,640
Rachel, you knew all this, right?

46
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,360
I didn’t know anything, what do I know about these things?

47
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:04,280
He has a little kid.
-They have a little kid, aren’t you ashamed?

48
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:07,400
Whatever, Menachem, whatever.

49
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,520
Just give me the "Bari," let me go.

50
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,600
Pull over, turn off the engine. What’s going on here?

51
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:15,520
Your wife’s crazy family. Has nothing to do with me at all.

52
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,800
Not your business. Listen to me carefully,
you’re not moving from here and getting nothing

53
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:21,720
until I understand what happened,
where you were and what you did.

54
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,720
Shh_

55
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,120
Your mom and my mom are the same mom.
-Okay.

56
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:31,560
What happened here?
-What happened here? A world fight, that’s what happened here.

57
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,880
By the way, did you notice Alin’s shoes,
how disgusting they are?

58
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,440
Sit down, can you calm down and explain to me what happened

59
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,760
and start from the beginning, please.

60
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,680
Okay, okay, so you took them downstairs.

61
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,600
Because you wanted Itamar and me to not be here alone,

62
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:44,120
by the way, he showed up right on time today,

63
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,880
did you notice that when he's without his wife
suddenly his watch works, right?

64
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,920
Sit down.
-What?

65
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Dude.

66
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,920
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

67
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,760
Come here, my sweet.

68
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,360
What's up?
-Shabbat Shalom. Yeah.

69
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,360
Shabbat Shalom.

70
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,200
Shabbat Shalom.
-Hey there.

71
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:05,480
Do you remember Itamar?
-Of course I remember, how could I forget?

72
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:08,040
I already apologized, right?
-Yeah, yeah.

73
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,800
Everything's been forgotten and forgiven a long time ago.

74
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,800
Come on, come in. Why are you shy?

75
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:13,760
Where's Shai?

76
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,000
He went to get your son,
he forgot him too.

77
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,400
What a fool.

78
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,320
What, are you here because he was scared to leave you alone?

79
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,240
Why would he be scared?
-I don't know.

80
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:24,240
Come on, who's scared? Nobody's scared.

81
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:27,600
Come on, I'll cut you a piece of mezhalof.
-Oh, tasty.

82
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,920
His brother, that's my family, right?
Watch your nonsense.

83
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,840
Stop it. What, are you a kid? Come on, sit down.

84
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,480
So from what you understood, Itamar's coming into the kitchen

85
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,120
for a piece of mezhalof.
-Yeah.

86
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,600
What does he want?
-His phone.

87
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,000
So why don't you give it to him?
-Because I want to know what he did.

88
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:47,120
So he ate the mezhalof and didn't like it.

89
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,000
What do you mean? Who said he didn't like it?

90
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:51,280
He threw you some comments, said something inappropriate.

91
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,040
He didn't say anything. Who said he didn't like it?

92
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,400
So what’s everyone fighting about?
-I don’t know.

93
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:57,360
I don’t understand these things.

94
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,640
I can't believe he didn't like the mezhalof.

95
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,480
He told me it was really tasty.

96
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,120
It's very tasty, uh...
-How nice.

97
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,600
Very.
-How nice.

98
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,600
So what's up? How are the parents, the kids?

99
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,480
Your wife?
-She's good.

100
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,360
I heard she got her license.
-Yeah, yeah, she had to

101
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:21,200
because she started studying
and I'm not driving her to class every morning.

102
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:23,080
Yeah, sure, sure, sure.

103
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,080
And how's business?

104
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:28,280
You know how it is in business.
-No, I don't know, what...

105
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,320
I don't understand these things.
-Yeah.

106
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,320
Hey, did you see the Mercedes outside?

107
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:35,840
Purple. What kind of car color is that? Who buys a purple car?

108
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,280
Your wife.

109
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,520
Wow, Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

110
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,800
Who is that? He looks familiar.

111
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,600
Shai's brother.
-Itamar.

112
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:47,560
Itamar.

113
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,800
Enjoy your meal.
-Thanks.

114
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,240
Isn’t he the one who broke up with you at the hospital?

115
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,400
Yeah.

116
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,040
What is this, an interrogation?
-No.

117
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,080
Just a few questions.

118
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:10,240
What happened? I feel guilty.
Please sit down, what’s wrong?

119
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,280
Relax, don’t stress.

120
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,960
Rachel told me you talked to my brother.

121
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,680
What, was that not allowed? No one told me.

122
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,240
He actually seems like a great guy, your brother, just so you know.

123
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,640
What's wrong with him?
-Everything's fine with him.

124
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:26,800
I want you to tell me everything that happened from the beginning.

125
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,520
So here’s the thing.

126
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,600
Where are we going to get 350,000 shekels now?

127
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:38,040
Don’t worry, babe, it’ll be fine, son.

128
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,640
We can manage like this, we can wait on the renovation.

129
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,640
I don’t want to, I don’t want to wait anymore.

130
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,520
Do you mind not starting with that
until after you’ve met my brother?

131
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,560
So just say it.

132
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,400
So here’s the thing.

133
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:53,440
So what, the Mercedes outside is yours, huh?

134
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,360
Yeah.

135
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,440
Great color.

136
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,480
You’re making a lot of money, huh?
-Come on, Moshe, enough. What?

137
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:02,200
No, it’s fine. You know, we’re making a living.

138
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:05,040
Why not? Cheers, what, I’m just curious.

139
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:07,480
Don’t you want your daughter’s husband to have a Mercedes too?

140
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:10,320
What do I know? I don’t understand these things.

141
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,840
So what, Itamar,

142
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,560
what do you do, if I can ask?

143
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:20,120
I’m an entrepreneur, real estate.
-Real estate is really hot these days, huh?

144
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,440
All the tycoons are in real estate now.

145
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,480
Where are you building?

146
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,960
I’m not building anything, I’m an entrepreneur.

147
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,680
Where’s the money from?
-Come on, Moshe. Enough, it’s not...

148
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,560
I had a few successful deals in Varna.

149
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,120
Where’s Varna?
-By the Adriatic Sea.

150
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,000
Where’s the Adriatic Sea?

151
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:45,840
Okay, Moshe, forget it, it’s really not that great.

152
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:49,320
For every successful deal, there are plenty that fail.
And

153
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,400
Of course, of course.
-Yeah.

154
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:54,680
So what are you working on right now?

155
00:06:55,440 --> 00:07:00,560
I have an office that deals with organizing
groups for purchasing agricultural land

156
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,520
that will eventually be approved for housing.

157
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,520
I’ve heard about those approvals.

158
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:07,800
You make a lot of money, huh?
-Come on, enough, let him eat, that’s enough.

159
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:11,880
You know, every deal has
its chances and its risks.

160
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:16,960
Right now, for example, we have a plot
that’s up for sale, something near Givat Ada,

161
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,840
it’s just waiting for final approval.

162
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,960
You realize that right now a dunam is 13,700,

163
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:24,600
but once it gets the approval,
it’ll jump to at least 350.

164
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,280
What do you say?
-Yeah.

165
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,480
What do you say?
-Yeah.

166
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:31,600
But Moshe,
not every deal is a good deal, there’s risk.

167
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,840
Of course, of course.
-Of course.

168
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,880
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

169
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,160
Come on, are you done playing detective?

170
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:47,160
Let me get out of here already.
-Not yet.

171
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,760
At least let me check if I got any messages.
After that, I’ll get back to you.

172
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:51,680
Did you call me?

173
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,960
Itamar, give us a moment.

174
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,480
Can you explain to me what happened from the beginning?

175
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,280
So here’s the thing...

176
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:03,680
Who loves Shabbat? Mom and Dad

177
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:08,160
Who loves Shabbat? Grandma and Grandpa

178
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,920
Who loves Shabbat

179
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,880
Me.

180
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,080
You.
-And you.

181
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:16,240
Almost the whole world.

182
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,080
Who loves to eat mezilof?

183
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,960
Me!

184
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,680
Not from this beginning.

185
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:26,880
I was on the balcony, Moshe shows up, at the conference,

186
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,680
closes the door

187
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:32,039
and asks me for money!

188
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:37,280
Manny, can you lend me some cash?
-No problem.

189
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:42,400
So what, I heard you talked to my brother.
'Right?

190
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,200
He's a really nice guy,

191
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,200
he and my son have a lot in common.

192
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,480
Owen...
-Why Owen?

193
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:51,720
I don’t know if you know,
but my grandfather, may he rest in peace,

194
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,840
was offered, along with his friends,

195
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:58,880
to buy twenty dunams of village land for an orchard.

196
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:03,120
Where that tall tower is, at the city gate, that one.

197
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:07,160
But my grandfather, poor guy, was a naive man, you know?

198
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,480
By the time he and his friends managed to gather the money,

199
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:13,680
then Chafif, one of his friends, his best buddy,

200
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,840
Eliezer Chafif,

201
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,840
he just cooked him on the whole deal.

202
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,520
He went to the land registry, signed as Chafif, and took off.

203
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:25,440
And stole the whole deal right under his nose, you get it?

204
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:29,280
About his pride in that tower,

205
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,720
it's "Chafif Towers," over there, at the city gate.

206
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:35,240
It used to be "Hasson Towers."

207
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:40,040
Silvan, are you telling the stories
about your grandfather's orchard again?

208
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:44,360
Tell me, come on, would you
buy an apartment from a contractor named Chafif?

209
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,480
Enough, come on, let him eat.

210
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,760
Eat, eat, finish the mezilof,

211
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,680
I have plenty of business stories for you.

212
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,960
Get out of my way already.

213
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,720
Chafif, Silvan.

214
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:02,200
Don't you dare say that name again, got it?

215
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,720
Chafif, he tells me.

216
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,760
He's completely lost it. He has a kid, a new baby,

217
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,280
and he's wasting my money like I don't know what.

218
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:14,000
Our expenses have gone up and Sivan is not a baby,

219
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:17,000
he's a growing baby, he eats, he needs toys

220
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:20,000
and we want to go on vacation, it's crazy.

221
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:21,960
What did you do?

222
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,560
What did you do?

223
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:29,000
What did you do?
-I lent Moshe some money.

224
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:32,560
Without asking me?
-Why ask you, babe? It's Moshe.

225
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,240
No one else is seeing that money.

226
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:37,400
It's family.
-It's not family, it's Moshe!

227
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,280
Oops, sorry.

228
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:43,240
Anyway, did you see that Sarav Av! Alin
!he's bummed about it.

229
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,480
So I decided I'm going to talk to him.

230
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,920
Sorry, I don’t want to interrupt

231
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,320
but Shai, I'm talking to you as an adult,

232
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,240
I’d like to please leave here.

233
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,480
No.

234
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,760
What happened?
-She got upset that I lent Moshe money.

235
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,520
And you gave it to him?

236
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,640
Tell me, what are you, crazy?
Don’t you remember the problem he has?

237
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,920
Put 250 shekels on "Maccabi Afula."

238
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,640
Put 400 shekels on Rexi.

239
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,200
שים לי 250 שקל על "מכבי עפולה".

240
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,680
שים לי 400 שקל על רקסי.

241
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:24,480
Put 1,600 on Tel Aviv,
23 degrees, partly cloudy to clear.

242
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,520
Here.

243
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
No way, I'm sure it's not for gambling.

244
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,520
Tell me, what are you, a fool?
So why is it if it's not for gambling?

245
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,960
Moshe!

246
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,000
They don't appreciate me enough in this family, Shai.

247
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,880
Why do you think that?

248
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,640
They won't let me fit in,

249
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,200
they're holding me back from growing.
They feel threatened by me.

250
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,600
Everyone here is closing deals

251
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:53,920
and exchanging info among themselves
like it's nothing, without explaining what's going on.

252
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,400
Wow, great.

253
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,480
Are you ready to explain what's happening?

254
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,880
I'm going for it, I want a dunam.

255
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:03,160
What, are you talking about the Givat Ada group?

256
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,440
No, no, no, no. Forget it, you don't want that.

257
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,440
Yes, I do.

258
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:07,400
No, no. Moshe, seriously,

259
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,960
I don't even have final approval for that group yet.
Just drop it.

260
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,560
I'm serious with you, Itamar,
you can trust me in business—

261
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,520
3,700, deal, I'm in.

262
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,640
Write down my number.
-I don't have a phone right now,

263
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:18,360
my "berry" is with Shai. That's why I'm here.

264
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,320
I'm writing yours, zero five...

265
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,400
Here.

266
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,400
We'll talk on Sunday.

267
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,080
So what, Itamar, mixing business with pleasure?

268
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,960
Buying a group, I hear.

269
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:36,480
Soccer?
-No way.

270
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,480
My office organizes buying groups.

271
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,760
Very nice.

272
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,800
I never understood what those groups are about.

273
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:47,320
They're businesspeople getting together
to buy properties together.

274
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,880
What do you say?
-Yeah.

275
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:53,560
I'm all for businesspeople
and property arrangements, of course.

276
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,480
So, how many friends are in each group?

277
00:12:56,560 --> 00:13:00,040
It varies, it can start with three friends,

278
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:03,360
a few dozen, a few hundred,
a few thousand, theoretically endless.

279
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,880
And practically?

280
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,320
Right now, there's a guy in the group with sixty members.

281
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:09,000
We're mainly talking about friends with money?

282
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,160
I really hope so.

283
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:14,480
So, are there special acceptance rituals
for these arrangements?

284
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,560
No, all you need is to have money.

285
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,640
Very nice.
-Very nice.

286
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:22,480
What's the success rate?

287
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:26,640
Tell me, did you know
that Moshe had a gambling problem?

288
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,160
Of course. What, didn't you know?

289
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,480
It got really weird.

290
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,440
Bro, I'm a bit short on cash,

291
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,960
can you put that on "Hapoel Usfiya"?

292
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:42,560
Bro, I'm a bit short on cash,
can you put that on Lassi?

293
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,120
Bro, I'm a bit short on cash,

294
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:48,160
put that on Be'er Sheva, 30 degrees hot and dry.

295
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,680
Bro, I'm a bit short on cash,

296
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:56,680
Here.

297
00:13:57,240 --> 00:14:00,080
I checked, it's really not for gambling.
-So why did he need the loan?

298
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:01,440
That's exactly what I asked them.

299
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:05,400
-What?

300
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,120
Tell me, Moshe, why
did you need the loan?

301
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:10,240
Manny, what's up? Why are you stressed? I'll get back to you.

302
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,600
I'm stressed? Remind you of your problem?
You didn't even know you had one.

303
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:15,160
What problem, Manny? I'm not betting anymore,
I haven't touched it in weeks.

304
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,560
I swear, I won't even do small bets.

305
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,040
Until I check it on Wikipedia first.

306
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:22,040
Moshe, you're not answering me, just say "yes" or "no."

307
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,520
Do you need that money to gamble?

308
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:27,240
Manny, I swear, I care about you,
with girls, I'm done.

309
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,000
I was weak, but now I'm strong.

310
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:32,920
Manny, this is a deal,
a financial deal, a real opportunity,

311
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:38,040
You put in 13,700 today. Soon
you'll have returns, at least 350.

312
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,840
A financial deal?
-A real one.

313
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:41,840
Listen to me, Moshe,

314
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:44,040
If I hear you touched that money to gamble,

315
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:47,400
I'll come down on you hard
with all my weight. You hear me?

316
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:50,680
No need, Manny, I swear, my word as Moshe Katz.

317
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,320
Can I go back inside?

318
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,640
I'm sorry, I have one more question for you.

319
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:01,040
I can't concentrate
when your brother is making poodle faces.

320
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:03,440
Maybe give him back the phone.
-I don't want to.

321
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,800
What do you know about Moshe's deal?
-What deal?

322
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,960
I don't know anything. I don't understand these things.

323
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:14,040
Can I go back inside?
-Okay, fine.

324
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,000
Thanks.

325
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,200
What's good for Nochi Dankner is good for Moshe Katz.

326
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,600
She's not lying, you know?

327
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:24,280
She really doesn't understand anything about this stuff.

328
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,480
Itamar, I want to talk to you.

329
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:30,360
Alin, I need a moment, but...

330
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,280
Rachel, I'm on my way to...

331
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,920
Sit down, don't be rude.

332
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,680
I want to get in on a deal for about ten acres too.

333
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:40,520
I thought you didn't understand this stuff.
-I don't, but...

334
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:43,920
My bank manager, my fund manager, and my accountant,

335
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,240
they know a lot about this, so they'll
talk to you on Sunday, okay?

336
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,160
Yeah.

337
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,440
Good, run, run, before it slips away.

338
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:59,200
I heard you were seen
saying to Shani that she's rude?

339
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:04,000
Maybe, I can't commit to that.

340
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,360
Meirav.

341
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,320
I don't remember.

342
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,960
Meirav.

343
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:17,120
What do you want to know?

344
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,960
Why did you tell her she's rude?

345
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,160
Sit down, I need help.
-What happened, babe?

346
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,560
I need a sum of money.
-Why, what happened?

347
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:30,000
Okay, you heard there's a
group of single men with money and assets.

348
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,600
So why do you need money?
-Entry fee.

349
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:35,560
Alright, how much is it?
-13,700 shekels.

350
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:36,720
How much?

351
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:40,600
It's an exclusive group of friends
made up of very private businesspeople.

352
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,680
Are you crazy? What, are you opening a brothel?

353
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:45,640
Were you even listening to me?
-I was listening, I'm not giving you that money.

354
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,920
Well, great.

355
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,160
So I don't get it,
are you joining this group or not?

356
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,760
No, thanks to Esther,

357
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,800
but your lovely brother agreed to help me.

358
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:56,960
Let him burn in hell.

359
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,720
Itamar was in the bathroom.

360
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,080
Itamar, I thought about it.

361
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:06,720
When I think about things
I think them through.

362
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:11,520
I also know that alongside the sting, there's honey
and your honey might not be my honey,

363
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,960
but for you, everything's business.

364
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,760
It's clear to me that for me to join

365
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:19,119
your lovely exclusive group,

366
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,720
I need to pay a laundry fee of 13,700 shekels.

367
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:25,760
What’s also clear is that money
will be worth a lot more in the future.

368
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:29,840
So here’s the deal, I’m making a one-time offer,

369
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:34,000
that you lend me the 13,700 shekels now,

370
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:39,280
and in the future, when that honey comes in,
I’ll give you, pay attention, 50,000.

371
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,600
Nice, right?

372
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:44,200
You want me to give you 13,000 shekels, basically?

373
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,160
How sweet of you.
-No.

374
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:49,240
You see, Shai? Not everyone’s a fool like you.

375
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:51,320
But, what’s your name?

376
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:58,000
So from what you’ve gathered so far, Moshe asked me for money,

377
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:01,400
Meirav asked you for money and then my brother,

378
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:03,800
and your mom has a fund manager.

379
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,920
If you say so, Sherlock Homeless.

380
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:08,040
So the shouting isn’t because of Itamar.

381
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,680
I told you that from the start.

382
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,920
It started with me after he talked to Moshe.

383
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:15,680
So, what did he say?
-Everything’s fine, nothing to worry about,

384
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,600
he got a tip about a good deal,

385
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:20,800
some buying group,
something! from some private businesses, something! like that.

386
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,520
But you know, it’s Moshe,
you can’t understand much from him.

387
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,000
Seriously, private businesses.
That sounds familiar to me this week.

388
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:26,800
Wait, are you talking about money?

389
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:31,000
You can’t talk about money on Shabbat
and you don’t mix money and family.

390
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:34,280
Rachel, do me a favor, stop getting involved.

391
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,720
I’m not getting involved, I’m not getting involved.

392
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,480
Well, what I did manage to understand
is that today they’re buying for 13,700

393
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,840
and when the compromise happens, it’ll be worth at least 350.

394
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,040
13,700?
-Yeah.

395
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,600
That amount sounds familiar to me too.

396
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:46,160
Shai, you can relax.
Trust me, it’s not for gambling, okay?

397
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,360
Alright, fine, got it, not for gambling.

398
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:52,000
But I hope you’re going to
get something from that at least 350.

399
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,840
What?
-No, are you completely crazy?

400
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,320
Don’t you get that with the money you’re giving Moshe

401
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,560
he’s going to get rich off your back?

402
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,400
Moshe!

403
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:01,960
What?

404
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,200
Come here, come here.
-What?

405
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:07,840
Tell me, you said in the end it’ll come out to
something like 350 at least, right?

406
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,760
At least.

407
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,840
Great, so tell me, am I supposed to get something from that

408
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,240
or am I just here to be your ladder for thieves

409
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:14,400
and wait for you behind the wall until you come back?

410
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,840
Why, why thieves, why talk like that, what.

411
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,880
Why did Moshe take money from you?
-He didn’t take, he borrowed.

412
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,680
But what, he wants to cut you out of the profits.

413
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:24,800
That’s exactly what happened to my grandfather.

414
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,120
Exactly.

415
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:29,680
They’re cooking you, Menachem, they’re cooking you.

416
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:31,200
You see, Shai, not everyone’s a fool,

417
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:32,680
there are those who are willing to help.

418
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,040
Manny, why are you talking like that?

419
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:36,040
You asked me for a loan, you said, no problem,

420
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:39,000
there’s a problem? No need. Well, that’s great.

421
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,480
He won't give it back to you, I'm telling you,
he won't give it back, you'll see.

422
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,640
Alin, just relax, okay?
-You shouldn't interfere at all.

423
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,960
Well, it's better to have a close friend than a faraway love.

424
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,280
Who's interfering?
-What happened?

425
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:52,600
You'll wake up and find
"Katz Towers" by the city gate.

426
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:55,840
My husband lends money to idiots, that's what happened.

427
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:58,400
You asked my brother for a loan?
-What loan, no way,

428
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,360
just an initial amount for investment, that's it.

429
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,880
And Manny just wanted to check.

430
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:05,520
Listen to what I'm saying
this is about you and me being partners.

431
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,760
But you're not willing to be my partner.
-Why are you interfering?

432
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,480
She's his sister, she can interfere.

433
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:12,040
Enough with this behavior, that's enough.
-I want to be part of the group too.

434
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:15,640
Rachel, you knew all this, right?
-I didn't know anything,

435
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:16,880
what do I know about these things?

436
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:19,960
They have a little kid.
-They have a little kid, aren't you ashamed?

437
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:23,040
Chill out, Menachem, chill out!

438
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,520
So all this mess, it's not because of Itamar?

439
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,040
No, you didn't listen to me at all, did you?

440
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:31,200
You see? Here, please, thank you, sit down,

441
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,440
I told you, it's not my fault at all,

442
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:34,360
it's your family's fault,
something's wrong with your family.

443
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:35,760
Yeah, they're messed up.
-No, they're crazy.

444
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,120
Nuts.
-No, it's a total loss.

445
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,240
Total loss.
-They need hospitalization, I'm telling you.

446
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,240
14

447
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:40,720
Give it.
-What?

448
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,960
Fun. What? It's my knee.

449
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,040
Take.
-Thank you very much.

450
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:46,200
Go home, go.

451
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,040
Ugh.
-What now?

452
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:49,960
I thought it was because of Itamar
so I could have solved it.

453
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,400
He would have apologized, everything would have been fine.

454
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,560
So, what now? Why are you making a big deal?

455
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:55,200
My family, they heat up
just as quickly as they cool down, okay?

456
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:56,760
It's not like your family.

457
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:04,200
Sorry, I just wanted to say goodbye
because I'm leaving, I got this.

458
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:07,840
And thanks for the hospitality,
it was really very...

459
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,840
Every time I meet this family

460
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:14,000
I say you have a family that really...
there's nothing like it,

461
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:17,680
really, all the... have a good week and salam.

462
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,880
Moshe, you see? Here, I got an email.

463
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,120
The Givat Ada project fell through. No approvals.

464
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,960
You see? I told you, that's how it is.

465
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:30,720
Oh, and Rachel, so I probably won't need
to call your fund manager,

466
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,320
so thanks and sorry.

467
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:34,000
So, have a week...

468
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:35,840
Good.

469
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,760
What do I know?

470
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:41,920
I don't understand these things.

471
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,480
It was fun today at Grandma's.

472
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:48,520
Of course, it's always fun, we love Grandma and Grandpa.

473
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:50,400
No, because everyone was screaming.

474
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:55,160
I told you that Itamar alone is trouble.
You should have kept an eye on him.

475
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:57,760
Yeah, and you should have
not forgotten about his knee.

476
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:00,720
Sorry, did I tell you or not to keep an eye on him?

477
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,040
I know them! I said it.

478
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:04,280
